description:
&lt;p&gt;The Security Department at Morriston Hospital are looking for responsible individuals to join the Security/Car Parking Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts will be 37.5 hours per week covering various shifts including weekends and nights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need good communication skills and must have a valid SIA license.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other duties include,being able to provide an efficient and professional Security/Car Parking service for the Health Board as part of the Security/ Car Parking Team carrying out a range of preventative and reactive routine, scheduled and ad-hoc Security/ Car Parking tasks on a day to day basis. To protect staff, visitors, patients and property. To undertake an active operational role as part of the responsive Security service under the guidance of the Security/Car Parking Supervisor or Senior Nursing Staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any queries please contact Simon Lockley on 01792 703112.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Simon Lockley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Security &amp; Car Parking Services Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Simon.Lockley@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01792 703112&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
